1900	20	student	male	the goal of this experiment was to see how the "correct" "incorrect" prompting affected your impression of an initially neutral stimulus - the image of Bob. Then, it was to see whether the answers you gave in the first portion of the block influenced your quick evaluations of certain words and images. For instance, did the participant make lots of mistakes when the image of Bob was paired with "good" words after the "correct" responses were all generally bad actions.	The room is very hot so if there is any way to fix that it might improve focus.